@Node Purpose "Purpose of this program"

 Purpose of this program
 =======================
 I wrote this program because I wanted to have a fast program to search
 in the FidoNet world nodelist with. The other programs I had seen were
 all  quite slow, so I decided to make QuickNS as fast as possible. On
 my old A500, it searches a 2 Mb nodelist in about 1:30 minutes using
 the Boyer-Moore algorithm, and that is quite good... :-)

 I cannot compete with the speed of programs such as "Scan", but you have
 to keep in mind that QuickNS also has to parse the nodelist in order to
 know which net a node is in etc.

@EndNode

